text.section:
The Consumer Protection Division shall consider the following in setting the amount of the penalty imposed in an administrative proceeding:
The severity of the violation for which the penalty is assessed;
The good faith of the violator;
Any history of prior violations;
Whether the amount of the penalty will achieve the desired deterrent purpose; and
Whether the issuance of a cease and desist order, including restitution, is insufficient for the protection of consumers.
